==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic; cognate with Old Saxon ''[[motan#Old Saxon|mōtan]]'' (Dutch ''[[moeten]]''), Old High German ''[[muozan]]'' (German ''[[müssen]]''), Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐌼𐍉𐍄𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmo:tɑn/}}

===Verb===
{{Latinx|'''mōtan'''}} (preterite-present: ''3 singular present'' '''[[mot|mōt]]''', ''present plural'' '''[[moton|mōton]]''', ''preterite singular'' '''[[moste|mōste]]''')

# to be [[able]]; [[may]]
# [[must]], have to

===Descendants===
*English: [[mote]], [[must]]

